  "text": "The most common source of paresthesia is peripheral neuropathy. Cutaneous afferents nerves are more volatile than motor axons, due to differences in their biophysical properties. These differences maybe include more persistent Na + conductance and inward rectification on cutaneous afferents, properties which probably give greater protection from impulse-dependent conduction failure but produce a greater tendency for ectopic activity [CITATION_1] .",
